               <p>I am a <rs id="t17780429-86-viclabel405" type="occupation">leather-seller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17780429-86-victim724 t17780429-86-viclabel405"></join>, and live within Aldgate. On the 24th of last month, I lost forty sheep skins and a deer skin dressed in oil; while I was backwards in the compting house the prisoner came in and took them off the compter and went off with them. I pursued him and took him with the skins on his shoulder.</p>



               <p>(The constable produced the skins which were deposed by the prosecutor.)</p>

               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>

               <p>I met a man with the skins; he asked me to carry them to Iron Gate for 6 d. and put them on my shoulder.</p>

               <p>
                  <rs id="t17780429-86-verdict406" type="verdictDescription">
